On Fri, 17 Mar 2000 10:53:32 -0800 (PST), 
Evan Langlois <evanlanglois@yahoo.com> wrote:
>Whats the status of the "Loading Linux from Linux" patch? 
See 
http://www.scyld.com/software/monte.html.
  "Two Kernel Monte is a
kernel module which allows Linux to load another kernel image into RAM
and restart the machine from that kernel. The loader supports initial
ram disks and passing arbitrary kernel command line parameters to the
new kernel."
